#   landlock        (sandboxing for chsr)
#   pest            (PEG grammar parser for chsr's command DSL)
#
# RootAsRole replaces sudo/su with role-based access control + Linux
# capability mgmt + per-command policy enforcement.  `dosr` is the
# do-as-root executor; `chsr` is the admin/role-editor tool with its own
# domain-specific subgrammar parsed via `pest`.
#
# === AXIS 165 OPENER — PCRE2 / Perl-flavor regex ecosystem ===
# Axis position: Rust=220 OPENS Axis 165 at slot 1/0/0.  Canonical Rust
# PCRE2 binding is `pcre2-rs` by Andrew Gallant (BurntSushi — also wrote
# ripgrep, regex, walkdir, memchr).  It wraps Philip Hazel's PCRE2 C library
# providing the Perl-compatible regex flavor including lookarounds, atomic
# groups, recursive patterns, conditionals — features the default Rust
# `regex` crate (NFA-based, no lookaround) intentionally omits.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=220   ← THIS FILE              (axis 165 OPENS, slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=220     ← next round              (axis 165 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=220 ← round after            (axis 165 CLOSES at triple-220, slot 1/1/1)
